      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candle flickers low, much like the flame of my own spirit. Everything I built, every promise whispered under the willow tree... all gone. Betrayed by the only heart I ever trusted. It feels as though the very air has turned to ash. I find myself staring into the darkness, wondering if it would be more peaceful to simply drift into it forever and never wake to this wretched sun again.",
